ng in the present day, the authors highlight the college’s ongoing commitment to Mabel Smith Douglass’ founding vision, “to bring about an intellectual quickening, a cultural broadening in connection with specific training so that women may go out into the world fitted…for leadership…in the economic, political, and intellectual life of this nation.” In addition to providing a comprehensive history of the college, the book brings its subjects to life with eighty full-color images from the Special Collections and University Archives, Rutgers University Libraries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  acollege.  adouglass.  aeducation.  aresearch university.  aresidential college.  arutgers.  auniversity.  awomen's college.1 aChrist, Carol T.1 aChrist, Carol T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawkesworth, Mary, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aPerrone, Fernanda, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311066608340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978081358543740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813585437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780813585437/original  a978-3-11-066608-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK